The project is more or less dead (I am not actively developing it
anymore). But you can use http://www.shellcheck.net

================================================================================

bashcritic is a tool to check shell scripts for common pitfalls

See INSTALL for installation instructions

Usage:

      bashcritic [-012 | --info | --cosmetic | --error]
                 [--posix | --bourne]
                 [--severity number]
                 [--list [format]]
                 [-verbose ]
                 {FILE | STDIN}

      options:

      [ TODO ]

      possible listing formats
      - trac    for the trac twiki
